I order from Flo in Grubhub weekly... the food is incredible.  Best veggie burrito I’ve ever had!  The Baja Fish Tacos are amazing too and love that it comes with a salad instead of rice.  Can’t wait to pay them a visit in person 🙂

My friend and I were in town over the weekend, and decided we wanted Meixcan food for breakfast. A friend suggested we tried Flo. As we were on the Mag Mile, we ordered an Uber and arrived in 15minutes. Considering the restaurant had only just opened, the place was very busy and had a happy atmosphere. Our server was polite and friendly and full of recommendations. We only ahd a main course, which was suffice. HAd the huevos rancheros, which were good and very filling, lots of flavour and nice spices. Would definitely return on future trips to the city.

Just wandered in here with my spouse looking for some breakfast. I ordered the Flo Original Burrito and was blown away by how good it was. Spinach tortilla stuffed with scrambled eggs, roasted poblano, pickled jalapenos, pico de gallo, cheddar cheese and sour cream with potatoes and black beans. I also added some cheeky homemade chorizo which was awesome.
Came here for a quick bite and a round of drinks.  The patio area is so cute! They had live music and made sure the temperature wasn't too cold.
I get take out from here often. Very good food, reasonably priced.

Ok let me start off by saying this. I only had the nachos with cheese, corn and black beans and the soup of the day. Nachos are horrible soup was good and Hibiscus margarita was excellent. This was the first place I ate visiting Chicago and I was disappointed as for as food😩

walked by and wanted to order take-out. Was told they are closed for the day. I said "sorry need to borrow a chair for a minute" - just wanted to take my large backpack off and retrieve my face mask inside then head out. Woman said "i'm rolling down the door now, no one's allowed to be here". I get it but really? I just need 30 secs of convenience to find my face mask. so unsympathetic.
Came here during COVID-19. They were very accommodating, clean, and friendly. Let us have drinks while we were waiting for a table. BBQ Pork sandwich & enchiladas were great.

Take out food during this weird pandemic is much needed and Flo does not dissappoint. We had chorizo mac and cheese (AMAZING), mole duck enchiladas (so flavorful!), and southwest cobb salad (yummy saved for lunch next day) from their limited menu. Don't forget drinks for the night. We had their homemade sangria which made our game night super fun! We ordered by calling and curb side pick up were happy with our experience.

Short wait for food. Really enjoyed the fish tacos- very light with creamy sauce. Server had recommendations for drinks and food. Cozy ambiance great for a winter day. Would be glad to visit again sometime soon!

Surprisingly good! Went there with a few friends because it was nearby and was surprisded by how good the food is. There isn't anything special about the interior or vibe but the food and service were great! I ordered the egg sandwitch and pancakes and loved both. Definitely recommended.
Coffee is amazing. Service is great. Food is delicious.  Love this place.

Came here for dinner with party of 5. Staff was great and we enjoyed the ambiance. Some of the dishes tasted too salty for our liking and dessert wasn't very fresh. Regardless, green chili enchiladas and mac & cheese are super tasty. Want this place to stay around. It's a great spot in the neighborhood!

My dinning experience from the wait staff to the food was outstanding. We arrived at Flo approximately 7:15pm on a Wednesday, it's the best time to go but parking can be an issue but the plusses are far greater than the minus. We were greeted with smiles and accommodated with a high chair for our infant. Alex, our amazing server was an absolute delight she prepared and served us cocktails and wine. I enjoyed a tasty Purple Haze Margarita. The starters that we enjoyed were Grilled shrimp Sopapillas, Shrimp tostada both made to perfection and Mac and cheese with fruit for the child. The entrees were simply prodigious. We enjoyed Chile Rellanos, I recommend you try it for yourself, it has a little kick to it. The presentation of each dish surpassed my expectations. I had to restrain myself from snapping a picture. As pretentious as it may sound the flavors just dance around in your mouth. The shrimp were juicy and tender the flavor is delectable. Flo is truly a treat, I highly recommend you treat yourself.

I was looking for authentic chilaquilles and a friend recommended this place unfortunately he was wrong about the authentic part although disappointed, the flavor of the dish did not fail! The dish had an over all great taste and I absolutely loved that they threw in some corn to add a different texture to the chilaquilles. I also love that they have “house bottled hot sauces” I recommend either the jalapeño or chipotle the habanero was kind of bland. Definitely recommend and would stop in again!

I do not understand what the hype is all about. Had to wait outside for 20 minutes to get a table (in Chicago. In November!) - true, lunch on Sunday can be a busy affair, but still.  The food was ok. Prices were ok. The coffee was ok.  I had the chicken enchiladas, my companions had the red chilaquiles, egg sandwich, and French toast with zabaione. Everything looked ok.  So I am not complaining per se, but the very high ratings are, in my opinion, not justified. The place is just ok. Not a place to travel any number of miles to. WOW!  I cannot believe this place has been here for TWENTY YEARS and I just found out about it!  I loved stuffed sopapillas when I lived in Denver or visited Santa Fe and this place has 'em! Both sopapillas I tried (shrimp with the green sauce, chorizo with the red) were stuffed and so good.  The Hatch green chile stew is almost enough for two people.  Definitely bring your appetite! The alcoholic drinks are also around $7, super cheap!

We were looking for a place for a family lunch to celebrate a birthday. Our sons all live near Goose Island, and this is only about 1/2 a mile away. They open at 9:00 am and have really good breakfast options. They also have hatch pepper sauce, which we had when we were in Colorado. The food was great and they had all kinds of unusual options. There were lots of vegetarian options, the Big shoulders coffee was very good, and the environment and the service was very good. We'll all be back!
Delicious breakfast at a great price!! We went on a Friday morning and there was no wait.

I was expecting this place to be an average brunch spot but with a fruity pebbles French toast option, I knew I had to at least try it once.  It's actually a solid brunch spot, everything we ordered was definitely above average.  Surprisingly, we didn't have to wait long (less than 10 mins).  We did call ahead and check what the wait time would be.  I had tried coming here last summer (without calling) and it was over a 2 hr wait at that time.  So definitely recommend calling ahead to check.  I've searched high and low for a good eggs Benedict in Chicago and this is the best one I've found so far.  We tend to order individual egg dishes and one sweet dish for the table, which is what we did with the fruity pebbles French toast.  It's the equivalent of red velvet French toast at yolk (without actually being red velvet).  A dish that's worth coming back for and hits the perfect sweet spot to end a brunch with flair.

This place is a great little place to eat. We have enjoyed anything we've ordered on the menu. The salmon was our favorite so far. The burrito and enchiladas are also great.  The staff is friendly and quick. There is a small outdoor patio if you feel like eating outside. The food comes out at the right speed so you know it was made to order. I personally like the house margarita. I never seem to leave without having two. The prices are reasonable.  Our last visit the staff was so good about working together to wait on tables. They really made the experience seamless.  #mexican #friendly #patio #restaurant

This is one of my favorite breakfast restaurants in the city. All the food is well prepared and the service is amazing. While I like all the food, the king for me is the Huevos Rancheros. I usually order it with the green sauce instead of the red sauce because i find that the green sauce is tastier and is a little bit more spicy. I also would recommend the french toast.

There is a perfect ebb and flow to the small place. But be prepared to bump shoulders and make a new friend. The staff is friendly and the service is prompt. The french toast flight or the super flight are must haves. No syrup needed ~ the fresh fruit toppings and homemade maple butter have that covered. Their homemade chicken sausage is to die for. Anything you try here is so good!

Stopped by for early lunch were served the most delicious vegetarian fare! We had veggie burrito, which was piping hot with cool fresh salad and salsa, portobello tacos, guacamole and homemade chips - so fabulous! We ate outside and our dog enjoyed fresh water and a biscuit :)

Our brunch experience at Flo was great! We went on a Sunday around noon. No wait at all. The service was great and all of the staff was very friendly. After being seated in a busy area of the restaurant, the hostess was very accommodating when we asked to be seated at a more secluded table. Even though we had already heard great things about the Fruity Pebble French Toast before going to Flo, it was much better than expected. We also ordered the Steak Eggs Benedict. One word sums up this item... AMAZING. The combination of poached eggs, sourdough bread and a healthy portioned cut of steak cooked to perfection makes this dish worth another visit to Flo in the near future!
Two thumbs up for this place.

Every plate we saw on other tables had potatoes leftover, and we soon realized why - not a ton of flavor and no crisp, they didn't serve much purpose aside from sopping up some sauce.

We came here because of the awesome photos of the French toast with cereal we have seen online. We ended up getting a coffee and the steak Benedict. The steak was overcooked and the potatoes were not that good. The sauces they had at the bar were very good and complimented the food well. They had a Chipotle, habanero, and a vinegar sauce. Awesome food, great value, good beer selection, local vibe.

I went here on a first date this past weekend after seeing Flo on a list of best places for brunch in Chicago. As soon as we were sat, our waitress immediately came over and asked for our drinks order, which she dropped off soon after. A few minutes later, she was back asking what we'd like to eat. We weren't ready (as we'd been chatting) and the server said she'd give us a few more minutes. I remember saying to my date, "I'd better look at the menu before she comes back again" and, lo and behold, a few minutes later she was back, asking if we were ready to order again. We were, with my date ordering the French toast and I the portabella tacos. The food arrived very quickly soon after. My tacos were adequate. Not bad, but nothing to write home about.  What bothered me about Flo is the service. Our server came over way too frequently. My date and I were having a conversation and she would interrupt us without waiting for a sentence to finish. Very rude.  This bothersome attention was because the server was rushing us through brunch so she could turn her tables over faster. We hadn't even finished our meals before the check was dropped off, which meant our waters and coffee were empty and our server completely disappeared until she came over to tell us it was time to leave as there was a line. We were barely in the restaurant an hour. Definitely not the relaxed brunch I was hoping for.  I'll be honest, I won't be returning to Flo and I plan to tell my friends to stay away. A server should never flat out ask me to leave but I guess because she'd already been given her tip, we weren't worth her time. Incredibly unprofessional.
Love the breakfast here. ( Fruity pebbles french toast)
Seating was a game of Tetris for the host but we were seated faster than our expected wait time. Always tricky w winter weather and people standing around inside. Amazing food!

The food was really good and they have some fun items on the menu like the popular fruity pebble toast.  You can order them individually for $3.50.  I didn't have trouble finding street parking on a Sunday afternoon.  Bloody Mary $7 - They offer 3 different types - cholula, chile rojo and chile verde.  I went with the classic cholula and it came garnished with a pepper and an olive and was very salty.  Huevos Rancheros $9 - Cheddar cheese enchiladas topped with chile sauce, 2 fried eggs and black beans.  The enchiladas were swimming in sauce, and I rather enjoyed it.  The sauce was very good and everything tasted fresh.  Fruity pebble french toast $3.50 - Delicious!  It not only looked pretty, but tasted great with the fruit on top.

Love this place! Delicious twists on great Mexican breakfast plates. I've had a breakfast burrito (that they were able to customize to be veggie friendly - thank you!) and the huevos rancheros. Both absolutely scrumptious. And their drinks are pretty stellar too. I do recommend getting there early on the weekends - the place gets packed pretty quick for obvious reasons. YUM!
Great upscale Mexican food with fantastic service. Highly recommend trying this place out!
Delicious Mexican-American food

We lived in Albuquerque for over 8 years and since moving away about four years ago, often missed New Mexican food. Flo definitely was a taste of home and was so good! We no longer have to wait to go home to eat red and green chile!
Aaamazing food and mimosas at a great price!

Flo is AMAZING! We visited Chicago and ate here every single morning of our trip. Everything was delicious, but our absolute favorite was the huevos verdes. Service was excellent. If I could give this place 10 stars I would. We had a wonderful trip, and still regularly discuss how we miss having brunch at Flo :)
Very friendly service, food came out speedily and tasted amazing. Drew is an affable bartender and made the experience great!
Was extremely impressed. Took my Mom, brother and girlfriend here for brunch. Food was delicious and my Mom is hard to please. Portions were large and prices were affordable. Great spot

The only New Mexican food I've found in Chicago.  The best things on the menu are the green chile cheeseburger and the green chile stew.  Native NM tip: get the plain sopapillas and ask for the bottle of honey to go along with it.  It's the authentic NM dessert!

Been to Flo's several times for brunch and dinner and the place does not ever disappoint. The cuisine and style is from New Mexico, not much cheese like Tex Mex but a lot of chili powder. Margs are refreshing and not syrupy or sugary. I have had several things on the menu and all have been 4-5 star quality.

Save your money for a flight to Santa Fe. This doesn't come close to anything in New Mexico. The majority of these reviews refer to this place as "Mexican" which tells you right off the bat they do not know what they are eating. I wanted so bad for this place to be good as I hope my last meal is a Green Chile Chicken Enchilada plate from La Choza in Santa Fe.

Had a quick brunch here before needing to be at the Amtrak station on canal. Only had 45 min to eat. Without asking for fast service, we were in and out. The beans were better than the potatoes. I had the Albuquerque turkey sandwich & it was delicious. Everything there looked tasty. I'll def be back. Oh & GREAT mimosas!
Great atmosphere. The food menu for brunch is broad with lots of options, but the brunch drink menu is limited. Mexican brunch dishes are mediocre.
Place is known for brunch but dinner is pretty solid. Try the flan dessert, amazing!
Delicious food and delicious drinks. The cocoa pebbles french toast and the triple berry french toast were amazing. Definitely coming back.
Delicious south-of-the-border flavored spin on a ton of classic breakfast mainstays. Looking for breakfast with a twist? Try out Flo!
Fast, friendly, reasonably priced, good food, great location, great ambiance.
Always reminds me of home, which is fantastic, and rare, in the heart of Chicago

My family is from New Mexico, and we're very particular about our cuisine, chiles and all. The dishes did not dissapoint! The space is beautiful, and the owner was very nice! If you've never had red chimayo Chile, come taste the difference!

I had a quick business lunch here. The food was great, the service was fast the price was right, ill definitely be coming back again. Mexican food has never been my favorite but Flo is so authentic the food is great!
The chilequiles are amazing! 💞
Delicious American, southern, Mexican food from scratch!
Food is 🔥
Always amazing food and service. Try the Verde Bloody, it's a unique take on a classic brunch drink staple. In house made salsas and bloody mixes. Very vegetarian friendly
Great breakfast selection. Mexican fare. Lots of sweet stuff. Potatoes are a bit bland.
Delicious food,affordable prices and friendly staff ,I highly recommend this place !
The menu is really good. They take basic Mexican dishes and transform them into something new. Yummy.
Excellent brunch place with vegetarian options and great mimosas. Usually gets packed around 11 am on the weekends, go early if possible.
Great for brunch! Love the menu and the friendly staff
Everything there is delicious 😋
Great brunch with a Mexican American flair.
New Mexico style cooking with emphasis on Hatch Green Chilies.  Big portions at reasonable prices.  My favorite is the green chili   chicken enchiladas.
Plenty of interesting dishes in brunch and dinner. Enjoyed Guadalajara Scramble with Big Shoulders Cold Brew. $10 Cocktails.
Year after year, always fresh and delicious.
Cozy with great food and great prices.
The breakfast here is amazing. Do not miss!
Amazing brunch went here on Sunday had the Huevos Verdes, Flo's Burrito and the triple Jerry French toast, music and the service are great!

Great service and delicious breakfast.  Started with Brioche French toast,  yummy.  Had their signature dish chicken enchilada with hatch salsa,  so good. Also tried the daily special, Egg  Benedict with ham, it was good.  Will Return.
You HAVE to order anything with the New Mexican red & green chili!  Their food belongs in your mouth!!  LOVE IT! Drinks? Yes please!

There was a small wait Saturday morning when we went. The host is very friendly. Prices are very reasonable for brunch and the service is quick. I really enjoyed the pulled pork tacos. I'll definitely be coming back here for breakfast/brunch on the weekend.
Decent brunch offerings w/ great service. This spot is always busy on the weekends.
Always delicious! Great daily specials.

Good place with tasty food. The place has a rustic feel with a hint of hipster-like vibe. **Please avoid having Brennan as your server as he will add more money to your tip than he deserves... Very shady guy.**
Food is great, mimosa flavors are delicious, and the chorizo tamale hash is the best Mexican brunch meal I've ever had!!!
Good food, quick service, good coffee and interesting breakfast bloodies.
Delicious food, great service, awesome cocktails!  Make sure to try the Cholula Bloody Mary if you are there for brunch.
The pulled pork tacos may be the best breakfast in the city.

Service was so so until the end and we didn't see our server for a while.  The place was not very busy during our time there.  Not much flavor in their dishes and it was very bland.  Definitely would not try this place again.
